    <stitle>CAB: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - DESCRIPTION - VEHICLE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER (VIN) TAG LOCATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>VEHICLE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER (VIN) TAG LOCATION</title>
        <para>VIN's are necessary if the need for replacement parts should occur. For this reason, you will want to know
            the location for these important numbers.
            <emph type="bold">Chassis</emph>and
            <emph type="bold">Cab</emph>VINs are located on the face of cab lock pillar, driver's side (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600702">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1600702" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1600702" filename="../figg16/G1600702.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 2. VIN Tag Location</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CAB DOOR OPENING PILLAR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CAB " VIN " TAG</callout1>
                <callout1>3. CHASSIS " VIN " TAG</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
